$ Oracle User Global Area
@ UGA

The *User Global Area* (UGA) is memory that is used for a session, as opposed to the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA[Process Global Area (PGA)] which is used for a
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes/server[server (=user) process].

In a *dedicated server environment*, the UGA is allocated from the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA, in a *shared server environment*, it is allocated from the SGA
(See → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/Large-Pool).

sa:

 → development/databases/Oracle/tools/oradebug/dumpvar[oradebug dumpvar uga …]

  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance
